The paper deals with optimization problems related to scheduling and routing, which are typical topics in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of approximation algorithms and computational complexity analysis suggests that the paper may also fit in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
